rivacy Policy Volca’s Studios Launcher

Last updated: 12-12-2025

Your privacy matters to us. This policy explains what data we collect, how we use it, and how we protect it.

1. Information We Collect
1.1. Account Information

Username

Email

Phone number (if provided)

Account creation method (Google Auth, email, etc.)

We do NOT have access to your password.
Passwords are encrypted and never stored in readable form.

1.2. Device Information

CPU, RAM, storage

Operating system and version

Crash logs

Performance-related information

1.3. Usage Data

Features used inside the launcher

Internal analytics to improve the app

2. How We Use the Data

We use your information only to:

Operate Volca’s Studios Launcher

Improve performance and user experience

Detect bugs, security issues, or abuse

Manage your account

We do not sell or share data with external companies.
All data usage is internal.

3. Data Security

We use modern security measures to protect:

Personal information

Device data

Account details

No system is 100% perfect, but we prioritize security seriously.

4. User Rights

At any moment, you may:

Request access to your data

Request correction of incorrect data

Request account deletion

Request that non-essential data collection stops

5. Data Retention

We only retain data for as long as necessary to:

Operate the service

Keep your account active

Meet legal requirements

Improve performance and security

If you request account deletion, we securely remove your data.

6. Policy Changes

If this policy changes, we will notify you through the launcher or our website.

7. Contact

For privacy-related questions or requests:
Email: dariovaz64@proton.me
